      "side": 1,
      "message": "Not necessary. If //prebuilts/clang/host/linux-x86/kleaf is in a subworkspace called `@kleaf`, then this evaluates to `@kleaf//prebuilts/clang/host/linux-x86/clang-{}:`.\n\nThe workspace name is important so we don\u0027t always refer to the main workspace. Note that `clang_toolchain` takes a string for clang_binary_prefix, not a Label (because it uses the string to construct a label string).\n\nThe more correct thing to do here is to provide each individual binary:\n\n```\nclang \u003d Label(\"{}:bin/clang\".format(clang_pkg))\nld \u003d Label(\"{}:bin/ld\".format(clang_pkg))\n...\n\nclang_toolchain(\n    clang \u003d clang,\n    ld \u003d ld,\n    ...\n)\n```\n\nbut it is an implementation detail within the same .bzl file, so I am taking the lazy route here.",
